    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offered for sale is a collector-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) in concours-ready condition. This example is powered by the S54 3.2L naturally aspirated inline-six, featuring six individual throttle bodies and a high-pressure double-VANOS variable valve timing system that has been fully serviced. The engine retains factory-spec compression across all cylinders and pulls cleanly to its 8,000 RPM redline. Power is managed by a 6-speed Getrag manual gearbox and a 3.64:1 limited-slip differential. Critically, the rear subframe mounting points have been professionally reinforced with plates, and the rod bearings have been replaced as preventative maintenance. The suspension features original Sachs dampers and fresh bushings, maintaining the precise factory kinematics. The interior is finished in Nappa leather with no bolster wear, and the undercarriage is free of oxidation. This is a turn-key, investment-grade machine for the technical purist.",
